   <text type="letter">
      <body>

         <opener>
            <dateline><name type="place" rend="right">Brooklyn, New York</name><date
               when="1871-07-14" rend="right">March 14</date></dateline>
            <salute>My dear Mr. Linton,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>I think of wanting this<ptr target="prc.00093_n1"/> engraved (exactly this size, and
            general design) for a frontispiece for my next edition of "Leaves of Grass." Do you
            think it would make a good picture?&#8212;Would it suit you to do it for me? If yes what
            would be the price?<ptr target="prc.00093_n2"/> I shall be here for some two weeks
            yet&#8212;then to return to Washington&#8212;</p>
         <p>&#8212;Send me word by mail, &amp; if convenient appoint an hour, day, &amp; place in
            New York, where we could meet &amp; talk it over&#8212;Bring this picture with you. I
            will be there as you appoint.</p>
         <closer rend="right">  
            <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
         </closer>

      </body>
   </text>
